caption: Table 1: Quantitative results for semantic binding assessment on various benchmarking subsets. We denote the best score in blue, and the second-best score in green
description: This table presents a quantitative comparison of different methods for semantic binding assessment.  It evaluates methods across three attribute subsets (color, texture, shape) using the BLIP-VQA metric and human preference scores (using ImageReward).  Additionally, it includes GPT-40 scores, evaluating performance on a new object binding benchmark. The best and second-best scores are highlighted for each attribute and metric.
